The government has declared dies non (no work, no pay) as part of its measures to tackle the token strike by State employees and teachers on January 12. An official release said here on Friday said employees and teachers would not be granted leave on January 12, other than for emergency situations such as illness of the person concerned or a close kin, examinations, etc. District Collectors and heads of departments should ensure that protection to employees who report for duty. The State Police Chief should make arrangements to provide security to government offices, the release said. The employees and teachers have decided to go on the token strike to press various demands including implementation of the State Pay Commission report.â€” Special Correspondent